ASABA – Aspirant for the 2023 Presidential Elections, Chukwuka Monye stated that only voting for the right candidate in 2023 would salvage Nigeria for economic collapse. Speaking yesterday in Onicha- Ugbo, Aniocha North Local Government Area of Delta State during the declaration of his intention to run for Presidency in 2023, he bemoaned the current state of the Nations economy saying that, Nigerians are at the high point of hopelessness and despair. He stressed need to reset the foundation of Nigeria into a true African Leader as it should be. 2019:  Nigerians Won’t Re-elect Almost All APC Leaders For… According to Monye, ” I wonder if our founding fathers will be content with the state of Nigeria”. Fundamental structures are at a brink of collapse with institutions such as health, justice and education and security infrastructure are unable to effectively meet the needs of the people”. He said that the challenge of economic stability can be solved by investing in what people are passionate about. Hence, he charged Deltans and Nigerians to play a positive role in altering the situation of the country. ” I represent a generation of Nigerians that has not witnessed what our parents told us about. I represent a generation that desires opportunities to express their innovative capacities. I represent a generation that desires justice, peace and equity” he declared.